President Obama has announced his intention to nominate Stephen Higginson to the United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit. Higginson has impressive legal and academic credentials, and a strong commitment to judicial integrity. He has served as an Assistant United States Attorney since 1989 and has received awards for his performance as a federal prosecutor. Higginson has also worked as an Associate Professor of Law at Loyola University New Orleans College of Law since 2004.